         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Gracemere ¶ Rockhampton ¶ Sept. 1st 1884 ¶ My dear Baron ¶  ¶ You will be surprised to receive a third communication from me after so short an interval....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.09.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Fred Byerley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eucalyptus tereticornis</seg> (MEL 707233). MS annotation by M: 'Answ | 9/9/84 | F.v.M.' Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Gracemere</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Rockhampton<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sept. 1st 1884</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will be surprised to receive a third communication from me after so short an interval.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Other letters not found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have been studying your ninth decade,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B84.04.04.</p>
               </note> and to day having gathered a specimen of E Tereticornis, or what I suppose to be such — our swamp gum, have been examining it by the light of your careful description</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In doing so I have remarked a peculiarity I have never before observed and of which there is no mention in your description — a Black Capsule <seg style="">3</seg>
               <seg style="font-size: 10pt; ">/</seg>
               <seg style="">16</seg> to ⅛<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>inch?</p>
               </note> deep, on the Calyx lid. from which it becomes detached apparently some time before maturity of the lid — or separation from the Calyx. (I am unaware if dehiscence is the proper term to apply) I send you specimens thinking it <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">possible</hi>
               </seg> that it may be a generic speciality peculiar to our Tereticornis altho the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">probabability</hi>
               </seg> is that it is not unknown to you</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With much respect</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Fred. Byerley</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Kindly <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">minute</hi>
               </seg> any remark you may have to make on the corner of this note — your time is too valuable for answers to your correspondents save in the most concise form</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron F. Von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20Tereticornis">Eucalyptus Tereticornis</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
